<p>Is it necessary to close ResultSet and PreparedStatement within one db.getConnection()? For the example below:</p>  <pre><code>Connection conn = db.getConnection(); PreparedStatement pstmt = conn.prepareStatement(firstsql); ResultSet r = pstmt.executeQuery(); // do something with the ResultSet r.close(); pstmt.close();   // do I need close the r and pstmt here? PreparedStatement pstmt = conn.prepareStatement(secondsql); ResultSet r = pstmt.executeQuery(); // do something with the ResultSet again r.close(); pstmt.close(); conn.close(); return null; </code></pre>  <p>Are the codes of line 5 and line 6 necessary?</p>